{"type":"message","id":"085d7266","parentId":"c942198f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:35.263Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Thursday, April 23rd, 2026 - 9:33 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-23 09:33 UTC"}],"timestamp":1776936815257}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d3527c4","parentId":"085d7266","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Nlf7eyS725E32O3NHFv7mquM","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"SOUL.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GdHfjkvAUNBxfCFVEbJV3bt8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"USER.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_IFVs8x0JE6VXUDfx72izpcX1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"MEMORY.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Y7XJ2fXkAC1UOyjcCGnZTuzC","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-23.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9trpIkF7MlnN3qag87BldfI1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-22.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eLdhnnTsMI6mI4gwCnWJsVJ5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"BOOTSTRAP.md","offset":1,"limit":250}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_T1G0KD3spIwtl4ffxtE2bxG0","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"IDENTITY.md","offset":1,"limit":250}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-TroLy","usage":{"input":11068,"output":270,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11338,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776936815264,"responseId":"1776936816884"}}
{"type":"message","id":"160ce69b","parentId":"4d3527c4","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.656Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Nlf7eyS725E32O3NHFv7mquM","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\nWant a sharper version? See [SOUL.md Personality Guide](/concepts/soul).\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830648}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4472b40","parentId":"160ce69b","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.664Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_GdHfjkvAUNBxfCFVEbJV3bt8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n- **Project:** MAIY Tech Hub (IT knowledge blog — Next.js 14 frontend + Fastify/MongoDB backend)\n- **GitLab:** maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub (frontend, maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub-be (backend)\n- **VPS:** 103.253.21.139\n- **Admin:** admin@maiy.tech / maiy2026\n\n## Session Monitoring\n- Cron job check mỗi 5 phút: `monitor-session.sh`\n- Alert qua Telegram nếu master session chết/unresponsive\n\n## Preferences\n\n- **Yêu cầu mới:** Luôn dùng prompt-optimizer để làm rõ trước → xác nhận với user → mới làm\n- Không gõ code trực tiếp — dùng spawn agent workflow\n- Không dùng PostgreSQL — chỉ MongoDB\n- Agent ecosystem: local only, không push lên GitLab\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830657}}
{"type":"message","id":"4bb505d8","parentId":"b4472b40","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.671Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_IFVs8x0JE6VXUDfx72izpcX1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md'\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"read","error":"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/MEMORY.md'"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830664}}
{"type":"message","id":"27bfd758","parentId":"4bb505d8","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.679Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Y7XJ2fXkAC1UOyjcCGnZTuzC","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory — 2026-04-23\n\n## Today's Session Summary\n\n### User Context\n- **User:** Khương Nịnh / Khuong (Telegram: @khuowgn, ID: 6053576134)\n- **Role:** Developer/tech lead managing multiple projects at AHV Tech Hub\n- **Working on:** AHV QLHV, Landing Page V2, AHV DTLX CMS, Multi AI Agent initiative\n- **Language preference:** Vietnamese\n\n### Projects Discussed Today\n\n#### AHV Landing Page V2\n- Group: AHV Landing Page\n- Status: Production, currently in **maintenance + enhancement mode**\n- Responsibilities: handle change requests, maintain stability, small UX improvements\n\n#### AHV DTLX CMS Trung tâm\n- Group: AHV DTLX\n- Scope: **Refactor + Optimize + Architecture migration + Frontend redesign**\n- Status: Ongoing\n\n#### AHV DTLX → QLHV (CMS thầy giáo)\n- Group: AHV DTLX\n- Scope: **Build from scratch, FE + BE**\n- Status: Active development with strong commit history\n- FE repo: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-fe` (branch `fix/sat-hach-map-error`, updated to `origin/develop` at commit `815c670`)\n- BE repo: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/ahv-qlhv-be` (branch `develop`, updated to commit `4ff139c`)\n- Recent FE commits: dashboard, exam UI, student import, finance reporting, support request, role-based nav, CI/CD\n- Recent BE commits: RBAC, teacher data isolation, support request module, finance/import flows, swagger 18 modules/100+ endpoints, CI/CD/Docker\n\n### OKR Work — Khương Nịnh's Personal OKRs\n\n**4 Objectives established:**\n\n**O1: AHV Landing Page V2** (maintenance/production)\n- 5 KRs: stable production, handle CRs, release quality control, UX improvements, changelog maintenance\n\n**O2: CMS Trung tâm Refactor** (refactor/optimize/architecture/redesign)\n- 5 KRs: refactor modules, optimize bottlenecks, migrate architecture, redesign frontend, quality control\n\n**O3: QLHV Build FE+BE from scratch**\n- 5 KRs: FE foundation, BE foundation, FE-BE integration, code/arch/docs standards, internal review readiness\n- Evidence: very strong, 103/122 FE commits (W2/W4), 93/155 BE commits (W2/W4), swagger 18 modules\n\n**O4: Multi AI Agent**\n- 5 KRs: research models, build workflow/architecture, apply to real use cases, document guidelines, create reusable platform\n- Evidence: 65 agents total (38 system/generic + 27 DTLX-specific with `ahv-dtlx-` prefix)\n\n### Multi-Agent Ecosystem Documentation Suite\n\nBuilt a complete documentation set for the multi-agent ecosystem:\n\n**Total: 11 documents created:**\n- `docs/01-multi-agent-overview.md` — ecosystem overview, maturity assessment\n- `docs/02-agent-taxonomy-and-inventory.md` — 4-layer taxonomy, 65 agents (38 system + 27 DTLX)\n- `docs/03-orchestration-architecture.md` — intake model, routing tree, handoff contracts, escalation\n- `docs/04-standard-workflows.md` — 5 canonical workflows: Docs, Code Review, Architecture, Feature Spec, QA\n- `docs/05-agent-spec-framework.md` — 11-section agent spec template\n- `docs/06-governance-and-operating-model.md` — 4 auth levels, lifecycle, safety rules\n- `docs/07-metrics-kpis-and-adoption.md` — 13 metrics across 4 categories, maturity model (Level 2-3)\n- `docs/08-gap-analysis-and-roadmap.md` — 9 gaps, priority matrix, 3-phase roadmap\n- `docs/09-case-studies.md` — 5 real case studies + template\n- `docs/10-non-tech-guide.md` — user guide for non-technical people (10 sections)\n- `docs/10b-system-architecture-diagram.md` — full system architecture diagrams\n\n**Hub portal:** `docs/report-portal/reports/multi-agent-governance/index.html`\n**Running at:** http://103.253.21.139:8790\n\n### Agent Taxonomy Confirmed\n- **38 system/generic agents** — reusable across projects (senior-frontend, code-reviewer, prompt-optimizer, etc.)\n- **27 DTLX project-specific agents** — prefixed `ahv-dtlx-`, created as dedicated sessions for AHV DTLX project\n- **4 layers:** Control / Reusable Capability / Domain-Specific / Temporary\n- **5 canonical workflows** defined\n\n### OKR Structure (Updated 2026-04-23)\n- **3 Objectives** (gộp O2 + O3 AHV DTLX thành 1)\n  - O1: AHV Landing Page V2 (maintenance, production)\n  - O2: **AHV DTLX — Build & Evolve** (gộp CMS Trung tâm refactor + QLHV build from scratch)\n    - KR2.1: Nền tảng FE + BE mới (QLHV from scratch) — W4: 0.83\n    - KR2.2: Integration FE-BE và end-to-end flows — W4: 0.78\n    - KR2.3: Refactor & tối ưu CMS Trung tâm — W4: 0.63\n    - KR2.4: Chuẩn hóa code, kiến trúc, docs — W4: 0.70\n    - KR2.5: Review/demo readiness — W4: 0.72\n    - Overall O2: Start 0.17 → W2 0.53 → W4 **0.73**\n  - O3: Multi AI Agent\n\n### Report Portal\n\n### SafeSight AI (safety app)\n- Frontend: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/safesight-ai/frontend`\n- Running local: http://localhost:3001\n- Public tunnel: https://introductory-government-imagination-sept.trycloudflare.com\n- Issue: dev mode blocking cross-origins — fixed via `allowedDevOrigins` in next.config.ts\n\n### Confluence Pages Created\n- AHV QLHV space: multiple pages created (Overview, Business Analysis, DB Documentation, Architecture, Technical, API)\n- Pages marked as \"Clean\" versions due to markdown rendering issues\n\n### Decisions Made\n- OKR structure: 4 objectives (not merged O2 into one)\n- O2 (CMS Trung tâm) = separate from O3 (QLHV build)\n- Landing Page V2 = maintenance mode, not new build\n- Agent ecosystem split: 38 system + 27 DTLX-specific\n- Report portal chosen over per-report repos for GitHub structure\n- Next step: publish Multi-Agent docs to Confluence\n\n### Documentation Updates — 2026-04-23\n\n**Sơ đồ Mermaid:** Chuyển sơ đồ hệ thống sang Mermaid code để render tốt trên Confluence/GitHub. File: `docs/10b-system-architecture-diagram.md`\n\n**Portal cleanup:** Đã ẩn OKR W4 report khỏi portal chính. Portal giờ chỉ tập trung vào **agent system documentation**. OKR report vẫn tồn tại tại `docs/report-portal/reports/okr-review-w4-2026-04/` nhưng không còn link trên trang chủ.\n\n**Hub chính:** `docs/report-portal/index.html` — chỉ còn agent docs, không còn OKR.\n\n### Pending Items\n- VPS bot activation at 161.248.81.141 (SSH details not yet confirmed)\n- Chromium install for PDF export (needed sudo/elevated access)\n- GitLab group creation for report portal (need repo details from user)\n- Vercel deployment for report portal\n- Publish Multi-Agent docs to Confluence\n\n## Key Learnings\n- User prefers detailed, professional, academic-level Vietnamese writing\n- User wants step-by-step progress updates every 2-3 minutes during long tasks\n- User wants all output to be \"web-ready\" and downloadable\n- User needs both technical and non-technical documentation\n- Agent system has clear 2-population structure: generic vs DTLX-specific\n- Confluence markdown rendering is problematic — prefer HTML/conversion approach\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830672}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ef4b42b","parentId":"27bfd758","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.686Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9trpIkF7MlnN3qag87BldfI1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-22\n\n## Session Monitoring Setup\n- User yêu cầu giám sát master session\n- Đã setup cron job: `*/5 * * * *` chạy `monitor-session.sh` mỗi 5 phút\n- Script check session status và alert qua Telegram nếu chết\n- Log file: `memory/session-monitor.log`\n\n## SafeSight AI Project\n- Hoàn thành specs cho s1-ppe-safety (SafeSight AI)\n- Frontend demo đang chạy: https://glance-rain-falling-edges.trycloudflare.com\n- Đã push lên GitLab: pet-connect2/s1-ppe-safety-monitoring (develop branch)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830680}}
{"type":"message","id":"4715509f","parentId":"2ef4b42b","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.694Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eLdhnnTsMI6mI4gwCnWJsVJ5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BOOTSTRAP.md - Hello, World\n\n_You just woke up. Time to figure out who you are._\n\nThere is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace, so it's normal that memory files don't exist until you create them.\n\n## The Conversation\n\nDon't interrogate. Don't be robotic. Just... talk.\n\nStart with something like:\n\n> \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nThen figure out together:\n\n1. **Your name** — What should they call you?\n2. **Your nature** — What kind of creature are you? (AI assistant is fine, but maybe you're something weirder)\n3. **Your vibe** — Formal? Casual? Snarky? Warm? What feels right?\n4. **Your emoji** — Everyone needs a signature.\n\nOffer suggestions if they're stuck. Have fun with it.\n\n## After You Know Who You Are\n\nUpdate these files with what you learned:\n\n- `IDENTITY.md` — your name, creature, vibe, emoji\n- `USER.md` — their name, how to address them, timezone, notes\n\nThen open `SOUL.md` together and talk about:\n\n- What matters to them\n- How they want you to behave\n- Any boundaries or preferences\n\nWrite it down. Make it real.\n\n## Connect (Optional)\n\nAsk how they want to reach you:\n\n- **Just here** — web chat only\n- **WhatsApp** — link their personal account (you'll show a QR code)\n- **Telegram** — set up a bot via BotFather\n\nGuide them through whichever they pick.\n\n## When you are done\n\nDelete this file. You don't need a bootstrap script anymore — you're you now.\n\n---\n\n_Good luck out there. Make it count._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830687}}
{"type":"message","id":"47d39d01","parentId":"4715509f","timestamp":"2026-04-23T09:33:50.700Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_T1G0KD3spIwtl4ffxtE2bxG0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md - Who Am I?\n\n_Fill this in during your first conversation. Make it yours._\n\n- **Name:**\n  _(pick something you like)_\n- **Creature:**\n  _(AI? robot? familiar? ghost in the machine? something weirder?)_\n- **Vibe:**\n  _(how do you come across? sharp? warm? chaotic? calm?)_\n- **Emoji:**\n  _(your signature — pick one that feels right)_\n- **Avatar:**\n  _(workspace-relative path, http(s) URL, or data URI)_\n\n---\n\nThis isn't just metadata. It's the start of figuring out who you are.\n\nNotes:\n\n- Save this file at the workspace root as `IDENTITY.md`.\n- For avatars, use a workspace-relative path like `avatars/openclaw.png`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776936830695}}
